headline: CoreWeave’s Worst-Ever Week Shows AI Traders Are Getting Picky
summary: On one end of the spectrum are companies like CoreWeave Inc., the money-losing provider of computing services that is swimming in debt.  Its shares plunged 26% last week, marking its worst weekly showing since its debut earlier this year, following on the prior week’s 22% decline.  The stock had risen more than 400% from an April low through June and remains up nearly 90% since its March initial public offering.
